The ATEX equipment directive (2014/34/EU) only certifies individual products/components for a defined protection concept (e.g., Ex d, Ex i, Ex e), gas/dust group, temperature class and ambient range. It does **not** address:
- how those items are electrically/mechanically interconnected (cable glands, barriers, earthing, segregation, intrinsically-safe circuit parameters, etc.);
- the actual zone classification, gas/dust composition or environmental stresses present at the specific site;
- cumulative effects such as heat rise, pressure piling, electromagnetic interference or maintenance-induce
